### Asset Export API Examples

# Note: Replace {{baseUrl}} with your actual API URL (e.g., http://localhost:3000)
# Replace {{authToken}} with your JWT token

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@authToken = your-jwt-token-here

### ===== EXPORT ALL ASSETS AS JSON =====

### Export all assets as JSON
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "json",
  "type": "all"
}

### ===== EXPORT ALL ASSETS AS XML =====

### Export all assets as XML
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "xml",
  "type": "all"
}

### ===== EXPORT SELECTED ASSETS =====

### Export selected assets as JSON
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "json",
  "type": "selected",
  "assetIds": [1, 2, 3, 5, 8]
}

### Export selected assets as XML
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "xml",
  "type": "selected",
  "assetIds": [1, 2, 3, 5, 8]
}

### ===== EXPORT FOLDER ASSETS (WITHOUT SUBFOLDERS) =====

### Export assets from a specific folder (no subfolders) as JSON
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "json",
  "type": "folder",
  "assetGroupId": 1,
  "includeSubfolders": false
}

### Export assets from a specific folder (no subfolders) as XML
POST {{baseUrl}}/assets/export
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "xml",
  "type": "folder",
  "assetGroupId": 1,
  "includeSubfolders": false
}

